<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4417] Checkpoints should be subsumed by CheckpointID not, by timestamp</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4417</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since the system clocks cannot be expected to be stable/monotonous, the subsumption logic in the checkpoint coordinator should not decide which checkpoint is &quot;newer&quot; based on the system time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The checkpoint ID is guaranteed to be strictly monotonously increasing. It is a better measure to decide which checkpoint is newer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
